## Architecture

Monorepo, MVVM on all platforms, API-first (OpenAPI -> typed clients).

{% if "backend" in platforms %}- **Backend**: Spring Boot 4, Kotlin 2.2+, Java 21 - Azure Container Apps{% endif %}
{% if "web-user-app" in platforms %}- **Web User App**: Next.js + TypeScript - Cloudflare Workers via OpenNext{% endif %}
{% if "web-admin-portal" in platforms %}- **Web Admin Portal**: Next.js + TypeScript - Cloudflare Workers via OpenNext{% endif %}
{% if "mobile-android" in platforms %}- **Android**: Kotlin + Jetpack Compose, Hilt, Retrofit 3, Room{% endif %}
{% if "mobile-ios" in platforms %}- **iOS**: Swift 6 + SwiftUI, async/await, Keychain, SwiftData (Mac/Xcode only){% endif %}

## Key Conventions

- API-first: define in `shared/api-contracts/openapi.yml` -> generate clients -> implement
- MVVM: one ViewModel per screen, sealed UiState/ViewState enum
- Repository pattern: interface/protocol + implementation
- Feature wiki pages in `knowledge/wiki/features/` — single source of truth for what to build
- Entity docs in `backend/docs/entities/`
- Auth: JWT tokens, OAuth ({% for m in auth_methods %}{{ m }}{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %})

## Product Wiki

Read wiki pages before implementing. Check `knowledge/wiki/index.md` first.

- `knowledge/wiki/index.md` - feature status board
- `knowledge/wiki/features/` - feature specs
- `knowledge/wiki/advisory/BOARD.md` - advisory board personas
- `knowledge/wiki/platform-requirements/` - platform-specific implementation notes
- `knowledge/wiki/business-rules/` - cross-cutting constraints

**Do not implement features without a wiki page.** Ask the user to run `po-intake` first.

